Organ trafficking in Russia has been a growing concern, with doctors accused of illegal kidney removal.
A new law aims to allow local hospitals to perform organ transplants, addressing the shortage.
Meanwhile, reports from Canada shed light on unethical practices in China, involving military hospitals.
In the Philippines, organ donation is a lucrative business, especially among the poor.
The US is expanding incompatible heart transplants for infants, while legal debates arise over incentivizing inmate donations.
Additionally, Zimbabwe plans to revive its organ donation program with strict regulations.
China also seeks to enact laws to streamline organ donation procedures.
